info.senderName: NWS Cheyenne (Southeastern Wyoming and Western Nebraska)
info.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 09 at 1:21PM MST until February 10 at 5:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 11 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 PM MST FRIDAY... * WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 MPH with gusts up to 65 MPH. * WHERE...Central Laramie Range and Southwest Platte County including Interstate 25 between Chugwater and Wheatland. * WHEN...From 11 PM this evening to 5 PM MST Friday. * IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Strong cross winds will be hazardous to light weight or high profile vehicles, including campers and tractor trailers. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Elevated winds gusting to 50 MPH may continue through early Saturday morning.
info.instruction: A High Wind Warning means a hazardous high wind event is expected or occurring. Sustained wind speeds of at least 40 MPH or gusts of 58 MPH or more can lead to property damage.
